structured.description: A constant function named `fn` that takes no arguments and returns no value. The function uses the `console.log` method from the browser's developer tools API to print the string representation of the number 0 to the console. The code does not have any dependencies on external libraries or packages, it is self-contained.

items.description: Logs the value "0" to the console when called. It is a constant function, denoted by the keyword `const`, which implies it cannot be reassigned. The arrow function syntax defines a concise way to declare a function that returns no value.
